page_title: How to work with prompt engineering and the Chat Completion API
page_description: Learn how to work with the Chat Completion API for prompt engineering.
chunk_content: Temperature and Top_p parametersChanging the temperature parameter changes the output of the model. The temperature parameter can be set between 0 and 2. A higher value, for example 0.7 makes the output more random and produce more divergent responses, while a lower value, like. 0.2, makes the output more focused and concrete. A fictional story could be generated using a higher temperature. Whereas to generate a legal document it's recommended to use a much lower temperature.Top_probability is another parameter and is similar to Temperature in that it also controls the randomness of the model response, but it does so in a different way. The general recommendation is to alter one of these two parameters at a time, not both.
